A collection of goodies for the Gnome2 desktop and its relations.

go is a universal command-line launcher for GNOME.
Much like gnome-open, but it can launch programs as well.
Always in a new window, always fully detached from your terminal.
$ go             # launch a new terminal window
$ go <file>      # open <file> in your preferred application
$ go <URL>       # open <URL> in your preferred application
$ go <CLI-prog>  # launch command-line program in a new terminal
$ go <GUI-prog>  # launch GUI program
$ go -g <words>  # launch google search for <words> in default browser

tapeta is a simple wallpaper slideshow program.
notgmail provides desktop notifications for new email on Gmail.

Use both tapeta and notgmail as Startup Applications.
